5:
Whoa! There's sand EVERYWHERE, as
far as the eye can see! Now THIS is
real adventuring.
9:
I've never seen someone get so
excited about sand...
12:
The desert is teeming with monsters,
so be on guard at all times!
16:
Haha! Don't worry, you can leave
EVERYTHING to me.
20:
Yeah... That's the wrong way,
though...
25:
All right, how about we make a stop
here?
28:
Please help my son, doctor! He's
terribly ill...
30:
I'm sorry, I want to help him, but
we've completely run out of
medicine here... There's nothing I
can do.
33: What seems to be the matter here?
36:
This man's son was bitten by a
venomous snake... Unfortunately,
we're out of the medicine needed to
treat it.
38:
What we're missing is the herb used
for the antivenom. Going out to
gather it is no use either, as we'll just
be attacked...
41:
If you had this herb, could you save
the boy?
47: In that case, leave it to me!
52:
Sorry, Alk. We'll be going our
separate ways here. If I make it back
to this town aliveâ€”
55:
What are you talking about, Grieg?
We're obviously going with you.
59:
B-but... I couldn't possibly force you
to do something like that...
63:
Nobody's being forced. We're going
of our own volition. We want to help
this boy as well.
68:
Okay, that's great! Thank you guys
so much!
71:
You can leave EVERYTHING to us, all
right? We'll get you those herbs!
76:
And he's gone... Without asking
where we need to go.
82: This seems like the right spot.
86:
Over there! There's no doubt about
it, we've found it!
92:
Look what we have here! Too bad
you guys are no match for us!
97:
Hahaha! Cleaned them up real
good, didn't we?
112:
No problem, we've defeated every
last one of them! Let's grab the
herbs and get going.
120:
I can't possibly thank you enough for
doing this... You've saved my boy!
123:
Haha... It was no big deal, really! This
is justâ€”
144:
Glad to see you're awake. You've
been out for nearly a whole day.
147:
Still, I can't believe you didn't tell us
you were bitten! You were moving
around all that time with venom in
your system...
152:
Just a moment longer and you
could have died, Grieg! Why didn't
you tell us?!
156:
I'm sorry, guys. I didn't want to be a
burden... I figured we didn't have
enough medicine for me, either...
165:
We have more than enough herbs in
stock now. We had the means to
treat youâ€”if we had only known you
were bit to begin with!
169: Oh... I didn't think of that...
171:
*sigh*... I haven't changed much
after all. I'm the same as I was back
then, getting yelled at by the other
villagers.
174:
I'm from a village out in the boonies,
you see. One with next to no other
young people my age. I got stuck
with having to help out all the
elderly...
178:
They always used to scold me.
You're so careless, you need to be
more careful, you need to use your
head more! Stuff like that.
181:
I... kind of see where they were
coming from.
185:
The one thing I had going for me
was my strength. So I decided to use
it and become just like one of those
heroes the elders always talked
about.
187:
That way, I could repay the debt I
owed them.
192:
A hero, huh. If you ask me, you've
already become one!
198:
Thank you so much for helping me. I
heard you brought the herbs we
needed...
200: Oh... Are you feeling better now?
206:
Because he rested as soon as he
found out he was bit. Unlike a
certain someone...
209:
You also beat up the snakes too,
didn't you? You're so cool...
210:
One day... do you think I can be as
strong as you?
214: Of course! Of course you can!
217:
But... you also have to learn to rely
on others! No matter how strong
you get, you can't do everything
alone!
